cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses a strategy for achieving an ideal distributed computing infrastructure and proposes a distributive lattice structure for resource sharing and an interprocess protocol. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper mentions guaranteed security as one of the goals of the ideal distributed computing infrastructure and introduces a hierarchical currency for authentication and access control. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses a partially ordered set of all data in the infrastructure to construct the distributive lattice structure. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses a simple language resembling a UNIX shell and a concept of execution for the distributive lattice structure. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper mentions minor syntactic adjustments to the algebra used in the distributive lattice structure.
